The paper deals with efficient detection in MIMO wireless systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The focus on hardware complexity and silicon area suggests a possible fit with computer systems and architecture (cs.SI). The analysis of computational complexity and algorithmic behavior also points towards systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
